         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Melbourne Bot Garden ¶ 5/1/71 ¶  ¶ The Capt. of the Ship "Geo. Thompson" has been so kind to promise to look after a small case full of plants, intended for you; ¶ See M to J. Hooker, January 1871 ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.01.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [Joseph Hooker]</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 1.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Correspondent assumed to be J. Hooker as the letter is informing Kew that plants had been sent. There is no other similar letter addressed to another Kew officer. MS annotation<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at head of letter: 'ansd thanked and list returned 19/4/71 J.S.' [John Smith (1821-88)].</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne Bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/1/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Capt. of the Ship "Geo. Thompson" has been so kind to promise to look after a small case full of plants, intended for you;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, January 1871 (in this edition as 71-01-00).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or rather his wife is to exercise the vigilance over them. Be so kind to send for the case, when the Ship arrives in London.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation beneath valediction: 'case received April 1871 only five plants alive J. Smith'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
